10:29.040 --> 10:33.760
But I probably shouldn't be talking
about booze, should I? [sighs]

10:40.920 --> 10:43.000
Rob, I hope you're not here
to talk about what I--

10:43.080 --> 10:44.160
It's about that, yeah.

10:46.280 --> 10:48.720
I've been thinking about it again,
that night.

10:48.800 --> 10:50.520
-[Mia] Rob.
-I can't not think about it.

10:50.600 --> 10:52.320
We said that we'd put it out of our minds.

10:53.400 --> 10:55.560
Weren't we just gonna try and keep it out?

10:56.800 --> 10:58.160
[Rob] I can't. I'm sorry.

11:01.240 --> 11:02.840
It was a long time ago.

11:02.920 --> 11:05.360
Well, in here, it's now.

11:07.040 --> 11:08.120
Yeah, I know.

11:09.680 --> 11:12.120
Why today?
Why is it preying on your mind today?

11:13.080 --> 11:15.320
-[Rob] There's a news story.
-A news story?

11:15.400 --> 11:16.360
[paper rustles]

11:16.440 --> 11:19.480
Uh, a featured article.
Well, whatever you call it.

11:19.800 --> 11:21.240
