Yeah, I'm proud of you.

19:43.800 --> 19:44.640
Yeah.

19:48.480 --> 19:49.480
I love you.

19:58.440 --> 20:01.320
-[clanging]
-[chattering]

20:04.560 --> 20:06.920
[chains jangle]

20:11.640 --> 20:14.640
[exhaling, grunting]

20:23.480 --> 20:26.080
[sizzling]

20:44.800 --> 20:46.960
[body crashing, sizzling]

21:26.360 --> 21:27.840
[typing]

21:27.920 --> 21:29.200
So that's one night.

21:29.280 --> 21:33.120
You had room service
and a £9.99 charge for the movie.

21:33.480 --> 21:34.800
For a movie?

21:34.880 --> 21:38.520
You... you watched a film last night, no?

21:38.600 --> 21:41.280
Yeah. I was in last night, yeah.

21:41.360 --> 21:42.320
[card reader bleeps]

21:45.560 --> 21:46.400
Thanks.

21:46.480 --> 21:48.080
-Thank you.
-[elevator dings]

22:09.840 --> 22:12.880
[alarm blares in distance]

22:46.560 --> 22:47.440
[knocking]

22:50.920 --> 22:53.640
I'm from Realm Insurance,
about the pizza van accident.

22:53.720 --> 22:54.840
[man] Oh, come in.

22:54.920 --> 22:55.920
[woman]<i> </i>I mean,

22:56.000 --> 22:59.720
it'll cover you for up to four months,
but that is quite a substantial claim.

22:59.800 --> 23:02.520
Well, I was heading off on tour
with the Philharmonic next week.

23:02.600 --> 23:04.880
Europe, Middle East, Australia.

23:04.960 --> 23:06.520
-Not now.
-Mm.

23:07.000 --> 23:09.280
